        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 2:35PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 235 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Long Mott, or near Seadrift, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Port Lavaca, Seadrift, Point Comfort, Placedo, Green Lake, Long Mott,
and Austwell.

This includes US Highway 87 between mile markers 824 and 840.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
